T1  - A Field Study of the Influence of Situational Constraints Leader-Member Exchange, and Goal Commitment on Performance
AU  - Klein, Howard J.
AU  - Kim, Jay S.
Y1  - 1998/02/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256900
DO  - 10.5465/256900
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 88
EP  - 95
VL  - 41
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the relationships between situational constraints, leader-member exchange, goal commitment, and performance in a retail organization. Both situational constraints and leader-member exchange correlated significantly with commitment to assigned goals, and an interaction between leader-member exchange and goal commitment accounted for a significant amount of variance in sales performance.
AB  - This study examined the relationships between situational constraints, leader-member exchange, goal commitment, and performance in a retail organization. Both situational constraints and leader-member exchange correlated significantly with commitment to assigned goals, and an interaction between leader-member exchange and goal commitment accounted for a significant amount of variance in sales performance.
