JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 108
EP  - 119
VL  - 41
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Results of this field study of 597 employees demonstrate the importance of extra-role behavior in explaining employee performance over a six-month period. Supervisors, peers, and employees differentiated in-role from extra-role behavior. They also differentiated two related forms of promotive extra-role behavior: helping and voice. The authors cross-validate their results and conclude by discussing future research implications.
AB  - Results of this field study of 597 employees demonstrate the importance of extra-role behavior in explaining employee performance over a six-month period. Supervisors, peers, and employees differentiated in-role from extra-role behavior. They also differentiated two related forms of promotive extra-role behavior: helping and voice. The authors cross-validate their results and conclude by discussing future research implications.
